The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Friday, June 13, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Friday, June 13, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, as the final phase of work on the AJC Bose Road flyover will be taken up. Buses and minibuses heading from Beckbagan to Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling east towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route. The crossover point between Gorky Terrace and Woodburn Park Road, however, will remain open to traffic, as will be the Lower Circular Road-Lansdowne Road and Lower Circular Road-Camac Street crossings..				 																Mango show				 																																	National Mango Show 2003 at Agri-Horticultural Society of India on 1, Alipore Road.				 																Season sale				 																																	An end-of-season sale featuring household accessories at Sasha, on Mirza Ghalib Street, from 10 am to 7 pm.				 																Workshop				 																																	A workshop on modern dance, theatre and creative expression at Padatik.				 																On display				 																																	A photographic exhibition on the Medieval City of Gaud at State Archaeological Museum.				 																																	An exhibition of pottery at Central Cottage Industries Emporium, 10 am.				 																																	A Sunil Das retrospective at ITC Sonar Bangla from 11 am to 7 pm.				 																																	Paintings and sculptures by members of Exposure at Academy of Fine Arts.
